actor Editor as Organization author/editor/admin
participant UI as React EntriesPage/PagesPage
participant Tenant as Auth and tenant middleware
participant Entry as Content routes
participant Plugin as Built-in plugin hooks
participant Validate as Sanitization/schema/workflow
participant Page as Page routes
participant RLS as RLS connection/transaction
participant DB as PostgreSQL
participant Cache as Redis delivery cache
participant Hook as Webhook dispatcher
participant Preview as In-memory preview channel
participant WS as WebSocket preview client

rect rgb(238, 247, 255)
    Note over Editor,DB: Content entry creation and update [IMPLEMENTED]
    Editor->>UI: Submit dynamic entry form
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/entries/{type_slug} with Bearer token and organization header
    Tenant->>Entry: Claims and TenantContext
    Entry->>Validate: require_org_entry_writer
    Entry->>DB: Check content quota for creation
    Entry->>DB: Load content type schema
    Entry->>Plugin: run_entry_before_save
    Plugin->>DB: Load enabled cms_plugins for organization
    Plugin->>Plugin: Run enabled built-in hook, including SEO mutation
    Plugin-->>Entry: Mutated entry JSON
    Entry->>Validate: Sanitize rich-text fields
    Entry->>Validate: Validate sanitized data against content type schema
    alt Role, quota, plugin, sanitization, or schema validation fails
        Entry-->>UI: Mapped error; no content entry write
    else Validation succeeds
        Entry->>RLS: Open tenant connection
        RLS->>DB: Set tenant session context
        Entry->>DB: INSERT content_entries as draft version 1
        Entry-->>UI: Created entry
    end

    Editor->>UI: Edit existing entry
    UI->>Tenant: PUT /api/entries/{type_slug}/{id}
    Tenant->>Entry: Claims and TenantContext
    Entry->>Validate: Writer role check
    Entry->>DB: Load type schema
    Entry->>Plugin: before-save hook
    Entry->>Validate: Sanitize, then schema validate
    Entry->>RLS: Open tenant connection
    Entry->>DB: UPDATE data and increment version
    opt Entry was already published
        Entry->>Cache: Best-effort invalidate content and sitemap keys
    end
    Entry-->>UI: Updated entry
    Note over Entry,DB: Entry writes use a tenant connection, not an explicit multi-write transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
end

rect rgb(238, 255, 242)
    Note over Editor,Hook: Entry workflow submission and publication [IMPLEMENTED]
    Editor->>UI: Submit draft for review
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/entries/{type_slug}/{id}/submit-review
    Tenant->>Entry: TenantContext
    Entry->>Validate: require_org_entry_writer
    Entry->>DB: Load current tenant entry
    Entry->>Validate: require_transition current -> pending_review
    Entry->>DB: UPDATE status, clear published_at, increment version
    Entry-->>UI: pending_review entry

    Editor->>UI: Publish entry
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/entries/{type_slug}/{id}/publish
    Tenant->>Entry: Claims and TenantContext
    Entry->>Validate: require_org_entry_publisher
    Entry->>DB: Load current entry and validate transition to published
    Entry->>DB: UPDATE status, published_at=now(), increment version
    Entry->>Cache: Best-effort invalidate delivery keys
    Entry->>Plugin: run_entry_after_publish
    Plugin->>DB: Load enabled built-in plugins
    alt After-publish plugin fails
        Note over Entry,Plugin: Entry is already published; no rollback exists [DECISION REQUIRED] AMB-070
        Entry-->>UI: Error after state mutation
    else Plugin succeeds
        Entry->>Hook: trigger entry.publish
        Hook->>DB: Load active subscriptions for organization
        Hook-->>Hook: Spawn one asynchronous dispatch task per subscription
        Entry-->>UI: Published entry
    end
end

rect rgb(250, 248, 255)
    Note over Editor,Preview: Page creation and manual save [IMPLEMENTED]
    Editor->>UI: Build new page and click Save
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/pages
    Tenant->>Page: Claims and TenantContext
    Page->>Validate: require_org_page_writer and content quota
    Page->>DB: Load component registry keys
    Page->>Validate: Validate title, slug, page_json tree, component keys, depth, and node count
    critical Page and initial snapshot transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Page->>RLS: Begin tenant transaction and set local RLS context
        Page->>DB: INSERT pages
        Page->>DB: INSERT page_versions complete page_json snapshot
        Page->>DB: COMMIT
    option Any write fails
        DB-->>Page: SQL error; transaction rolls back
        Page-->>UI: Mapped error
    end
    Page->>Preview: Broadcast committed page_json
    Page-->>UI: Created page

    Editor->>UI: Edit existing page and click Save
    UI->>Tenant: PUT /api/pages/{id}
    Tenant->>Page: Claims and TenantContext
    Page->>Validate: Writer role and complete page request validation
    critical Page update and snapshot transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Page->>RLS: Begin tenant transaction
        Page->>DB: UPDATE pages title, slug, and page_json
        Page->>DB: INSERT next complete page_versions snapshot
        Page->>DB: COMMIT
    option Update or snapshot fails
        DB-->>Page: SQL error; both writes roll back
    end
    Page->>Preview: Broadcast committed page_json
    opt Page remains published
        Page->>Cache: Best-effort invalidate page, pages, sitemap, and robots keys
    end
    Page-->>UI: Saved page
end

rect rgb(245, 255, 245)
    Note over Editor,Hook: Page workflow submission and publication [IMPLEMENTED]
    Editor->>UI: Submit page for review
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/pages/{id}/submit-review
    Tenant->>Page: TenantContext
    Page->>Validate: require_org_page_writer
    Page->>DB: Load current tenant page and validate transition to pending_review
    Page->>DB: UPDATE status and clear published_at
    Page->>Preview: Broadcast current page_json
    Page-->>UI: pending_review page

    Editor->>UI: Publish page
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/pages/{id}/publish
    Tenant->>Page: TenantContext
    Page->>Validate: require_org_page_publisher
    Page->>DB: Load page and validate transition to published
    Page->>DB: UPDATE status and published_at=now()
    Page->>Preview: Broadcast current page_json
    Page->>Cache: Best-effort invalidate page delivery keys
    Page->>Hook: trigger page.publish
    Hook->>DB: Load active subscriptions
    Hook-->>Hook: Spawn one dispatch task per subscription
    Page-->>UI: Published page
    Note over Page,DB: Status-only transitions do not create page_versions snapshots [IMPLEMENTED] AMB-069
    Note over Page,Hook: Cache/webhook side effects occur after the page mutation [DECISION REQUIRED] AMB-070
end

rect rgb(255, 252, 238)
    Note over Editor,DB: Debounced autosave [IMPLEMENTED FOR EXISTING PAGES]
    Editor->>UI: Mutate page_json in builder
    UI->>UI: Mark draft dirty
    alt Draft has no persisted page ID
        UI-->>Editor: Manual save required before autosave
    else Existing page and not currently saving
        UI->>UI: Reset 10-second debounce timer on each mutation
        UI->>Tenant: PUT /api/pages/{id} after 10 seconds
        Tenant->>Page: Same update and snapshot flow as manual save
        Page->>DB: Transactionally update page and insert a new version snapshot
        Page-->>UI: Autosaved response
        UI->>Tenant: Reload pages/components and later request versions when selected
        Tenant->>Page: Tenant-protected GET requests
        Page->>DB: Read tenant-owned pages, components, or snapshots
    end
end

rect rgb(255, 244, 238)
    Note over Editor,Preview: Version restore [IMPLEMENTED]
    Editor->>UI: Restore selected snapshot version
    UI->>Tenant: POST /api/pages/{id}/versions/{version}/restore
    Tenant->>Page: Claims and TenantContext
    Page->>Validate: require_org_page_manager and positive version
    Page->>RLS: Open tenant connection
    Page->>DB: Load tenant-owned page_versions snapshot
    Page->>DB: Load component registry keys
    Page->>Validate: Revalidate snapshot page_json
    critical Restore transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Page->>RLS: Begin tenant transaction
        Page->>DB: UPDATE page_json, status=draft, published_at=NULL
        Page->>DB: INSERT restored content as a new version snapshot
        Page->>DB: COMMIT
    option Restore write fails
        DB-->>Page: Transaction rolls back
    end
    Page->>Preview: Broadcast restored page_json
    Note over Page,Cache: Restore does not call delivery cache invalidation even when replacing a published page [PARTIAL]
    Page-->>UI: Restored draft page
end

rect rgb(238, 250, 255)
    Note over UI,WS: WebSocket live preview [IMPLEMENTED, IN-MEMORY]
    UI->>UI: Build ws(s) URL with access_token and organization_id query values
    UI-->>WS: Share/copy preview URL
    WS->>Tenant: GET /api/preview/{page_id}?access_token=...&organization_id=...
    Tenant->>Tenant: Verify JWT, active organization, and active membership
    Tenant->>Page: WebSocket upgrade with TenantContext
    Page->>Preview: Get/create page-specific broadcast sender
    Page->>DB: Load initial tenant-owned page
    Page-->>WS: Initial page_json message
    loop While socket and process-local channel remain active
        UI->>Tenant: Manual save, autosave, restore, or workflow transition
        Tenant->>Page: Authorized tenant request
        Page->>Preview: Broadcast page_json after mutation
        Preview-->>WS: Updated page_json message
    end
    Note over Preview,WS: Channels are process-local and not durable across backend replicas/restarts [PARTIAL]
end
